::Q1::Which Playwright API is used for file uploads? {=setInputFiles ~waitForDownload ~createReadStream}
::Q2::Which event is used to handle native file chooser dialogs? {=filechooser ~dialog ~upload}
::Q3::Which method waits for a file download to start? {=page.waitForDownload ~page.waitForEvent('download') ~route.fulfill}
::Q4::Which download property returns the target filename? {=suggestedFilename() ~filename() ~name()}
::Q5::Which method saves a downloaded file to disk? {=download.saveAs ~download.write ~download.store}
::Q6::Which API lets you upload files from buffers? {=setInputFiles with buffer ~uploadBuffer ~fileFromMemory}
::Q7::Which Playwright action triggers drag‑and‑drop uploads when input is hidden? {=dispatchEvent dragover/drop ~page.upload ~file.inject}
::Q8::Which test ensures file size validation works? {=oversized file rejection ~PDF header check ~CSV header check}
::Q9::Which magic bytes identify a PDF file? {=%PDF ~PK ~CSV}
::Q10::Which magic bytes identify XLSX files? {=PK ~PDF ~ZIPX}
::Q11::Which API reads downloaded file content as a stream? {=download.createReadStream ~download.read ~download.stream}
::Q12::Which folder should store generated downloads? {=playwright-downloads ~downloads-temp ~user-files}
::Q13::Which method clears an existing file selection? {=setInputFiles([]) ~clearFiles() ~resetInput()}
::Q14::Which method is best for multiple file uploads? {=setInputFiles with array ~uploadAll ~attachFiles}
::Q15::Which Playwright API is used for multipart file uploads via API? {=request.post with multipart ~page.post ~file.upload}
::Q16::Which method checks if a downloaded file failed? {=download.failure ~download.error ~download.failed}
::Q17::Which file type validation test uses magic bytes? {=binary checks ~header length ~timestamp}
::Q18::Which function parses CSV files for data‑driven tests? {=parseCsv ~csvToJson ~readCsv}
::Q19::Which strategy ensures stable UI when animations exist? {=inject no‑animation CSS ~block JS ~disable service worker}
::Q20::Which scenario verifies round‑trip export→import? {=Export CSV then import same file ~Upload invalid then retry ~Download then preview}